        <h1 class="Heading1">Introduction</h1>
        <p><span class="VariablesProductName">DigitalEdge</span> offers the ability  to search and retrieve data from a Lucene platform in near real time. Implementing search can be done  several ways to interact with Lucene:</p>
        <ul>
            <li value="1">Using the <span class="VariablesProductName">DigitalEdge</span> Search App (see the <span class="VariablesProductName">DigitalEdge</span> <i>Configuration </i>or <i>Operations </i>documentation). The Search app operates on top of the Lucene index and uses the Search API to access and query the index. </li>
            <li value="2">Using code which creates and sends an <code>HTTP GET</code> command (see <a href="sample_code.htm" class="MCXref xref" xrefformat="See &quot;{paratext}&quot;">See "Sample Code"</a>); or using a web browser with the appropriate URL</li>
        </ul>
        <p>The Search API provides search services to all these options. It performs distributed searches, which means that multiple Lucene nodes can be searched at the same time. This is accomplished by using the Solr distributed search functionality.</p>
        <p>You can access the Search API on the webapps.main machine at: <code>http://default.&lt;system_name&gt;/searchapi</code></p>
        <p>The Lucene index is located on the datasink.lucene machine in <code>/mnt/rdafs/lucene/index</code>.</p>
